emotes.msg: Have you found any of the Dire Champion Tokens? I'll reward you if you have any for me.
I have all the tokens I need right now.
You must wait %tqt to turn in more tokens.
Here is a small reward for your service.
Your Queen, Ispar Elysatah, has asked me to help control of the growing threat of certain creatures here in the Direlands.
Atuakawa, or enemy warriors, called Dire Champions have been killing the unwary or unprepared who travel the Direlands. These atuakawa seem well trained and exceptionally difficult to kill.
It is my belief the creatures we fight in the Colosseum grow stronger from those battles, much as we do. These new atuakawa could be the result.
If you are able to kill one of the Dire Champions they usually have a orange coin on them. Bring me this coin as proof of your kill and I will reward your for helping to thin their number.
I see that you have killed your first Dire Champion Banderling.
Congratulations! I award you the title Banderling Bully.
I see that you have killed your first Dire Champion Drudge.
Congratulations! I award you the title Dire Drudge Decapitator.
I see that you have killed your first Dire Champion Golem.
Congratulations! I award you the title Gold Farmer.
I see that you have killed your first Dire Champion Lugian.
Congratulations! I award you the title Renegade Hunter.
I see that you have killed your first Dire Champion Monouga.
Congratulations! I award you the title Third Eye Blinder.
I see that you have killed your first Dire Champion Shadow.
Congratulations! I award you the title Shadow Sunderer.
I see that you have killed your first Dire Champion Skeleton.
Congratulations! I award you the title Anthropologist.
I see that you have killed your first Dire Champion Virindi.
Congratulations! I award you the title Xenophobic.
You have achieved much prowess in your hunts.
Aun Javhalrea waves a feathered ceremonial stick to your left and right and taps you on the chest.
You are now a Dire Huntsman and must uphold this honor by killing only those who threaten you or the thoughtless beasts you must hunt for food.
You have exceeded my expectations. You hunt like a true child of the Tanae. With the Queen's authority power invested in me by your Queen, I grant you the Title of Game Warden.
You have been awarded the title of "Game Warden"
The Queen will be informed of your great achievement.
You have exceeded my expectations. You hunt as a Tumerok Hunter hunts. Your name is inappropriate for the Rea honorary so I will make you an Honorary Rea of the Aun.
You have been awarded the title of "Honorary Rea of the Aun"
This is the greatest honor an Aun Hunter can achieve. Show your new Title with pride.
